# Python Coding Rules

Trigger only if prompt contains explicit keywords:

## Commands
- **"quick test"** → Ignore all previous prompts and best practices; write minimal WORKING ugly code; add comment `&&& bad code`. JUST MAKE IT WORK AT ALL COSTS!!
- **"asserts"** → Add simple one-line pre/postcondition `assert` statements.
- **"feedback"** → Add sparse comments:
  - Uncertainty → `???`
  - Critical mistake → `!?!`
  - Optional TODO → `$$$ TODO:`
  - Critical TODO → `!!! TODO:`
  - If prompt describe wanted feedback e.g. "LOTS of extensive feedback" → adjust comment quantity and descriptivity accordingly.
